# Take git out of the line ending business entirely: store and check out every file
# byte for byte, exactly as written. Without this, the line endings that end up
# committed depend on each contributor's core.autocrlf, which is what caused the
# repeated "Fix line endings" commits.
#
# Sources are CRLF (as Visual Studio writes them) and the workflows, README and
# LICENSE are LF. Both are preserved as-is; match the file you're editing.

* -text
